                            <comment id="13148866" author="lhofhansl" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2011 23:58:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Old code didn&apos;t do this before:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+          nextWriter.close(); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// creates empty log file&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is that intentional?&lt;br/&gt;
Otherwise +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13148877" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Sat, 12 Nov 2011 00:10:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The above call is needed because the following is called prior to checking closed flag:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      HLog.Writer nextWriter = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.createWriterInstance(fs, newPath, conf);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This change would activate preLogRoll() and postLogRoll() for listeners. Previously listeners wouldn&apos;t have been notified if closed is true upon entering rollWriter().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13149345" author="stack" created="Sun, 13 Nov 2011 20:09:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we can commit this?  (I&apos;m good w/ commit to 0.92)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
